cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the security vulnerabilities in intelligent vehicle data sharing and proposes a blockchain-based solution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of biometric information, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The proposed framework involves the use of blockchain technology, which falls under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the reliability of data sharing, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
